Eco startup aims to offer 1000 vetted low-carbon solutions 
March 14, 2016
ClimateStore wants to make choosing low-carbon products simple and easy by curating and vetting each product for its carbon impact. When it comes to reducing the climate impacts of our daily lives, some of the solutions are easy and free (such as turning off lights when you leave the room, or choosing to ride your bike instead of drive), while others will require a bit more effort and money (such as replacing lightbulbs with LEDs, installing low-flow showerheads).
