view all press  & quotes










People Want to Stop Climate Change
It’s true. People want to stop climate change. But the problem is many don't know where to start. Our mission is to make it easy. We're building a one-stop-shop for climate change that integrates products, educational resources and more. Our goal is to help people achieve the future we all desire.




























The Movement Is Growing
With each passing year more and more people are convinced that climate change is real. They are realizing that climate friendly living is essential to preserve the natural world we have all come to know. They are searching for solutions and taking positive action. And the good news is – there’s still time to act.



















WE MAKE IT EASY
It's what people want. No more endless searching on the web bouncing from resource to resource. At ClimateStore you can learn about climate change, shop for solutions and make a personal plan. Our core mission is to make it easy to live a climate friendly lifestyle - and we're just getting started.
















Low Carbon Products From Mission Aligned Suppliers
To date we've sourced over 400 low carbon products from 30 suppliers. We organized them into over 40 categories integrating them in blog posts and action plans. We're extremely excited about the pipeline of products from new and existing suppliers who are expanding their eco-friendly offerings.

















Fully Reviewed for Climate Impact
We rank all of our products based on impact. To help sort things out, we developed icons we hope will make things easier. We review all our products for carbon impact and award icons to those that produce fewer greenhouse gases (GHGs) in either the production, use and/or disposal phases of their lifecycle. We also award icons when products produce their own renewable (green) energy, save money or have educational content. And just for fun, we have an icon for staff favorites!



















A Growing Community
We're just starting to grow our community, in the short time short time we've been active on social media, we've grown to a community of ~25K followers, newsletter subscribers and customers. But we're most excited about the quality of mission climate change aligned institutions that are following us.













Long Term Potential & Growth
We believe that ClimateStore has broad potential as a multichannel brand. The five year business model includes revenue streams from direct website and mobile sales, e-mail remarketing, affiliate programs and marketplaces. Affiliate revenues through partnerships are possible with membership driven environmentalorganizations, home energy audit contractors and possibly utilities. Additional could come from referral relationships (e.g. home solar and wind), carbon offset relationships, rewards marketplaces and catalog sales.













How Your Investment Will Help Us
Great content, products and user experience are critical to becoming a world class resource for climate consumers. As such, content generation is our near term focus and what your investment will support. Reaching the target will support product sourcing, curation, and expansion of the ‘take action’ portion of our website. We plan on relaunching our blog, weekly newsletter and primary social media channels. To gain the most impact from the investment, we plan on using a lean model which leverages a network of freelance content experts. Funds in excess of the target we will accelerate content generation using this scalable approach. Marketing efforts will focus on newsletter and community growth on social media channels. With great products, growing awareness and relaunched e-mail marketing we anticipate growing sales momentum. The attached ‘use of funds’ document provides additional details.




































OUR NEXT STEPS: BUILD DEEP CONTENT AND COMMUNITY

       We've been making steady process since founding, but now it's time to notch things up. The first two years were focused more on developing our brand message and early community. We've build a robust Ecommerce site, developed our brand persona and done some test marketing to get feedback. We've learned a lot and gotten some great feedback along the way. With this phase complete, we're excited about deepining our offerings and with enough resources kicking off our go-to-market strategy.
    




