Details

 Expand all



                  What is your traction to date?
                  



Even with minimal advertising and an early version of the website, there is early evidence of traction and reception for the brand. This can be seen through growth on social media channels, early sales, robust brand association and customer/follower feedback from primary market research.The brand currently has ~30,000 followers across social media channels and a growing mailing list of ~4,000. With modest effort, the company was attracting 1000-1200 followers a month on twitter and 500/mo on Instagram. Aside from a few pilots, the company has not executed a robust marketing effort to date.We are extremely pleased with the quality of organizations 'following' our social media channels which includes a broad range of environmental, green business, educational, government and international organizations. These have included progressive brands like Ben & Jerry’s, Unilever, Audubon, Treehugger, Rainforest Action Network (RAN), Earth Institute, MIT CoLab, US Fish and Wildlife Service, NASA Goddard Institute, KQEDScience, CeresNews, CarbonBrief, NetImpact, OceanWire and many more.Quarterly sales growth hit a peak of ~28% (12-15% ave mo/mo sales), with only pilot advertising and a non-optimized website. As of 12/31 the company had ~500 orders with $42,000 in revues from ~400 customers. Average order value was $96 for a 12 month period in 2015 and about 5% of customers were repeat buyers without any remarketing. Optimization of the site and implementation of the go-to-market strategy, including professional PR, should accelerate revenue and growth on social media channels.




                  How are you going to make money?
                  



Revenues in the next 18 months will come from direct website sales of products, e-mail marketing,  affiliate partnerships/programs, and 1-2 marketplaces.  Future channels include catalog sales, direct B2B, stores-within stores and brick and mortar stores.  Starting average margins are 46% with a plan to increase to 55% in 4-5 yrs. The current mix of products is 50/50 warehouse/dropship network with a goal of increasing the ratio over time. Use of social media and inbound will decrease % paid ad spend over time.



                  How do you acquire customers?
                  



Our go to market strategy leverages 1.5 years experience with targeted digital advertising, primary market research and social engagement. We have experience reaching out to target customers and the climate community. Tactics include: 1) targeted marketing on social media channels, 2) search engine marketing at the product, category, and issue level, 3) issue display ads on targeted websites, 4) professional PR, 5) low cost sponsorships and 6) affiliate relationships with mission aligned organizations. KPIs include email signups, remarketing lists, orders and conversion rates.




                  Does ClimateStore have international potential?
                  



Climate change is a global issue. We're already seeing customer interest from around the world. With additional resources we look forward to expanding in North America and will certainly consider international opportunities through partnerships and other mechanisms.




                  How will you have social and environmental impact?
                  



Climate change has been described as the greatest breakdown is scientific communication in human history. There is also a false perception that low carbon living is about giving things up. Our goal is to build a positive stylish vision of a climate friendly lifestyle. Sure, we don’t have Exxon's PR budget, but through creative content and community engagement, over time we seek to have a positive impact on social behavior – supporting, educating and encouraging sustainable living in all aspects. The resulting impact will be tangible reductions in carbon emissions through the products and information we offer, and by building and important sales channel for low carbon start-ups seeking to bring products to market.




                  Are you selling any private label products?
                  



No. But we hope to in the future and think the ClimateStore brand will work well in some categories.




                  Why should I invest?
                  



The timing for a climate focused brand couldn't be better.Despite recent political events in the US, climate change is a mega trend with rapidly growing public and media focus. With the recent adoption of the COP21 agreement, focus will now turn to the important task of actionable steps to rapidly reduce emissions to meet challenging goals.Individuals will be looking to do their part.There is a timely opportunity for a broad-based omni-channel brand that will serve consumers who are either considering, starting down, or well along the path of low carbon living. ClimateStore is a first-in-class brand which has never wavered from its low carbon mission and commitment to serving customers interested in protecting the climate.For the climate conscious impact investor, the company has significant potential to drive the climate conversation, raise public awareness about sustainable living, and be a leading channel for the many innovative companies developing consumer facing low-carbon products.













